    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan I've designed after thoroughly exploring the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan: Ollama Model Rename\n\n**4 files to modify, 0 new imports needed anywhere.**\n\n### What I found in the codebase\n\n- `CopyRequest` in `api/types.go` is the exact template for `RenameRequest` — identical two-field structure (`Source`/`Destination`)\n- `Client.Copy()` in `api/client.go` is the exact template for `Client.Rename()` — same `c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, ...)` pattern\n- `CopyHandler` in `server/routes.go` already does the JSON-bind → `model.ParseName()` → `.IsValid()` → `CopyModel()` pattern\n- `DeleteHandler` in `server/routes.go` already does the `manifest.ParseNamedManifest()` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` pattern — `RenameHandler` reuses both\n- All imports needed (`manifest`, `model`, `errtypes`, `errors`, `os`, `io`, `fmt`, `gin`) are already present in `routes.go`\n- `copyCmd` cobra definition and `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` call are the exact templates for `renameCmd`\n\n### Summary of changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `api/types.go` | Add `RenameRequest{Source, Destination string}` after `CopyRequest` |\n| `api/client.go` | Add `Rename()` method POSTing to `/api/rename` after `Copy()` |\n| `server/routes.go` | Add `RenameHandler()` (bind→validate→409 check→copy→delete→200) + register `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after `/api/copy` |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `RenameHandler` func + `renameCmd` cobra command + register after `copyCmd` in `AddCommand` |\n\n### Key design decision\nThe destination-already-exists **409 Conflict** check uses `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` — if it returns `nil` error, the destination exists and we abort. This happens **before** the copy attempt to fail fast cleanly.",
